The United States and France have a long-standing alliance and friendship, dating back to the French Navy's support of George Washington's forces during the American Revolution. The two countries continue to work together to enhance the security of their countries, the Transatlantic region, and the world. They collaborate on operational issues around the world, focusing on combating terrorism and developing regional capabilities to increase security and stability. They also work together to combat piracy and promote maritime security. The United States and France maintain an active training and exercise program to enhance the interoperability of their forces. They also have a personnel exchange program and support each other in NATO exercises. The two countries partner on space security, cybersecurity, defense procurement, nuclear security, and countering nuclear terrorism. They are committed to working together to strengthen their collective efforts and improve security measures to reduce the risks of nuclear terrorism.